   A
41-year-old zama zama boss was shot dead in Zanghoma village in Limpopo. The
zama zama boss was reportedly from Carvinal City in Ekurhuleni and had come pay
his ‘illegal mining’ employees.  The police and the medical emergency services were called to the scene and the
man was certified dead.  He
was identified as Frank Moyo, a Zimbabwean national.  The police have launched a manhunt for the suspect involved in this matter and appealed
to anyone with information that can lead to his arrest to contact Colonel Cecil
Machimane on 082 451 7181.  